1
00:00:10,200 --> 00:00:11,300
<i> I'm begging you.</i>

2
00:00:11,433 --> 00:00:12,667
<i> Take back your statement.</i>

3
00:00:12,800 --> 00:00:14,200
<i> Tell the truth.</i>

4
00:00:14,500 --> 00:00:17,000
<i>Why are you insisting
that I took a bribe?</i>

5
00:00:17,300 --> 00:00:19,100
<i>I thought you were a decent man.</i>

6
00:00:19,333 --> 00:00:20,333
<i> A good father.</i>

7
00:00:20,467 --> 00:00:23,000
<i>Can you really send an innocent
child to jail?</i>

8
00:00:23,133 --> 00:00:24,567
<i> Manuel was here earlier?</i>

9
00:00:24,700 --> 00:00:25,767
<i> I didn't sell you out.</i>

10
00:00:25,900 --> 00:00:28,367
<i>My private investigator
found something.</i>

11
00:00:28,500 --> 00:00:30,967
<i>This might help with our plan
to discredit Timo.</i>

12
00:00:31,100 --> 00:00:33,367
<i>Oh, Manuel,
Noah has good news.</i>

13
00:00:33,500 --> 00:00:34,600
<i> Yes, I heard.</i>

14
00:00:34,767 --> 00:00:35,967
<i>He's the hero again,
and you're all happy about it.</i>

15
00:00:36,100 --> 00:00:37,100
<i> Bro, what's your problem?</i>

16
00:00:37,233 --> 00:00:38,333
<i> You are the problem!</i>

17
00:00:38,467 --> 00:00:40,400
<i>You keep meddling
in my family's affairs!</i>

18
00:00:40,533 --> 00:00:42,367
<i>I don't think you even need
my help here.</i>

19
00:00:42,500 --> 00:00:43,333
<i> Really, Manuel?</i>

20
00:00:43,467 --> 00:00:45,233
<i>You're letting your pride
take over?</i>

21
00:00:47,133 --> 00:00:48,133
Noah!

22
00:00:49,533 --> 00:00:50,433
Noah.

23
00:00:57,733 --> 00:00:58,667
Why?

24
00:01:00,667 --> 00:01:04,333
I'm sorry if I took your help
the wrong way.

25
00:01:04,767 --> 00:01:06,233
I was just emotional.

26
00:01:06,367 --> 00:01:10,533
I was angry because my talk
with Timo didn't go well.

27
00:01:11,133 --> 00:01:13,067
And then I felt useless,

28
00:01:13,200 --> 00:01:14,900
like I can't do anything
for my kid

29
00:01:15,033 --> 00:01:16,300
while you...

30
00:01:17,833 --> 00:01:18,867
Anyway.

31
00:01:19,233 --> 00:01:20,900
I'm really sorry, man.

32
00:01:22,067 --> 00:01:23,000
Okay.

33
00:01:24,533 --> 00:01:25,933
Apology accepted.

34
00:01:27,767 --> 00:01:28,600
Thanks.

35
00:01:29,667 --> 00:01:32,533
I hope you'll still help Coleen.

36
00:01:33,633 --> 00:01:34,767
Of course.

37
00:01:36,667 --> 00:01:37,433
Okay.

38
00:01:48,400 --> 00:01:50,433
Son, I'm sorry.

39
00:01:51,567 --> 00:01:53,033
It's okay, Dad.

40
00:01:54,033 --> 00:01:55,467
I understand.

41
00:01:56,833 --> 00:01:58,133
Next time...

42
00:01:58,267 --> 00:02:00,900
don't let your emotions
get the best of you.

43
00:02:09,000 --> 00:02:10,033
Jessica.

44
00:02:10,167 --> 00:02:11,767
<i> Why are you sad, sweetheart?</i>

45
00:02:11,900 --> 00:02:13,067
<i> I love you, Dad.</i>

46
00:02:13,200 --> 00:02:15,533
<i>Please forgive me,
mommmy and me.</i>

47
00:02:15,700 --> 00:02:17,733
<i> Please forgive us, Dad.</i>

48
00:02:17,867 --> 00:02:19,400
<i> Take care of mommy, Dad.</i>

49
00:02:19,533 --> 00:02:21,367
Jessica.

50
00:02:22,400 --> 00:02:24,267
Jessica...

51
00:02:24,400 --> 00:02:25,233
Jessica...

52
00:02:25,367 --> 00:02:27,400
- Manuel, Manuel.
- Jessica!

53
00:02:28,533 --> 00:02:29,933
You're dreaming again.

54
00:02:31,300 --> 00:02:32,600
Was it Jessica?

55
00:02:33,900 --> 00:02:34,833
Yes.

56
00:02:36,267 --> 00:02:38,867
Same as before, but this time,

57
00:02:39,000 --> 00:02:40,900
it wasn't as clear.

58
00:02:43,267 --> 00:02:44,967
What are you doing here?

59
00:02:46,167 --> 00:02:48,767
I just wanted to ask
Jeffrey something.

60
00:02:49,833 --> 00:02:51,633
And I also wanted
to talk to you.

61
00:02:52,767 --> 00:02:57,000
I don't want to go to bed
angry at you.

62
00:02:57,800 --> 00:03:02,633
Felma, I'm sorry about what
happened earlier with Noah.

63
00:03:03,900 --> 00:03:05,767
Jeffrey talked to me.

64
00:03:06,867 --> 00:03:11,167
He told me what happened
between you and Timo.

65
00:03:12,567 --> 00:03:16,633
Yes, but that's still not
an excuse for how I acted.

66
00:03:17,667 --> 00:03:22,200
Honestly, I was jealous.

67
00:03:23,633 --> 00:03:25,767
You don't have anything
to be jealous of, Manuel.

68
00:03:26,800 --> 00:03:30,633
Whatever happened between Noah
and me was a long time ago.

69
00:03:30,767 --> 00:03:32,300
It's over.

70
00:03:33,533 --> 00:03:34,467
You're not mad anymore?

71
00:03:35,600 --> 00:03:36,733
You apologized.

72
00:03:37,800 --> 00:03:38,867
We're fine.

73
00:03:40,133 --> 00:03:44,200
There's no point holding
a grudge.

74
00:03:48,033 --> 00:03:50,600
Oh, by the way...

75
00:03:51,833 --> 00:03:53,333
Noah called.

76
00:03:54,600 --> 00:03:56,933
He's going to continue
helping us.

77
00:03:59,433 --> 00:04:00,267
Okay.

78
00:04:01,800 --> 00:04:03,100
Go back to sleep.

79
00:04:20,467 --> 00:04:22,367
Sweetie, thank you.

80
00:04:22,500 --> 00:04:24,433
You visited me in my dream.

81
00:04:26,400 --> 00:04:30,067
But why is it always like that?

82
00:04:31,733 --> 00:04:34,867
It keeps repeating
and you're always crying.

83
00:04:36,167 --> 00:04:40,233
And you keep telling me
to forgive you and your mom

84
00:04:40,367 --> 00:04:42,767
and to take care of her.

85
00:05:05,400 --> 00:05:07,733
I visit Jessica every day.

86
00:05:09,000 --> 00:05:12,100
And every night, she visits me
in my dreams.

87
00:05:12,233 --> 00:05:13,833
She keeps telling me that...

88
00:05:15,500 --> 00:05:17,300
everything will be fine.

89
00:05:18,433 --> 00:05:22,900
She also said she visits you,
too, and asking you...

90
00:05:24,800 --> 00:05:30,967
to forgive me
and to take care of me.

91
00:05:33,833 --> 00:05:35,700
Is that what
you dreamed of, too?

92
00:05:35,867 --> 00:05:36,833
Yes, Manuel.

93
00:05:38,000 --> 00:05:39,967
She was crying so hard.

94
00:05:40,100 --> 00:05:44,100
That's why when I woke up,
I was crying, too.

95
00:05:45,500 --> 00:05:47,000
Why, Manuel?

96
00:05:47,133 --> 00:05:49,467
Does Jessica visit you
in your dreams, too?

97
00:05:49,600 --> 00:05:53,700
Did she tell you her last wish?

98
00:05:55,533 --> 00:05:56,833
Her last wish?

99
00:05:57,833 --> 00:06:01,733
She said she wants us
to get back together.

100
00:06:03,500 --> 00:06:07,367
To rebuild our family,
even if she's gone.

101
00:06:11,200 --> 00:06:13,300
She never said that in my dream.

102
00:06:14,367 --> 00:06:16,500
And she would never say that!

103
00:06:22,667 --> 00:06:23,633
Well...

104
00:06:25,333 --> 00:06:26,533
It's just a dream anyway.

105
00:06:27,600 --> 00:06:30,333
I didn't expect you
to believe me.

106
00:06:31,833 --> 00:06:33,833
But she told me something else
in that dream.

107
00:06:36,433 --> 00:06:37,433
She said...

108
00:06:39,133 --> 00:06:40,567
she wasn't pushed by Coleen.

109
00:06:41,700 --> 00:06:45,867
That she wants her sister
to be cleared.

110
00:06:46,000 --> 00:06:47,400
No.

111
00:06:47,533 --> 00:06:49,700
It pains me because I disagree.

112
00:06:50,800 --> 00:06:54,167
I believe Coleen pushed Jessica.

113
00:06:55,367 --> 00:06:56,600
Didn't we even have a witness?

114
00:06:56,733 --> 00:06:58,800
Yes, someone you bribed to lie!

115
00:06:58,933 --> 00:07:01,767
Manuel, what are you saying?

116
00:07:03,000 --> 00:07:04,900
My conscience is clean.

117
00:07:05,767 --> 00:07:08,967
I had nothing to do
with Timo's statement.

118
00:07:10,500 --> 00:07:13,133
But I can convince him.

119
00:07:14,567 --> 00:07:17,567
I can convince Timo
to clear Coleen,

120
00:07:17,700 --> 00:07:19,233
and to grant Jessica's wish.

121
00:07:21,000 --> 00:07:22,333
- Convince?
- Ouch!

122
00:07:22,467 --> 00:07:23,667
Convince?

123
00:07:25,100 --> 00:07:28,267
Just admit that you can pay him
off to lie again!

124
00:07:31,467 --> 00:07:32,167
Manuel, what are you doing?

125
00:07:32,300 --> 00:07:34,100
Let go! You're hurting me.

126
00:07:34,800 --> 00:07:36,167
What's wrong with you, Manuel?

127
00:07:36,300 --> 00:07:38,233
Can you just listen to me first?

128
00:07:38,567 --> 00:07:42,533
I can convince Timo
through his wife, Diana.

129
00:07:43,467 --> 00:07:44,967
Hazel, stop it, please.

130
00:07:45,400 --> 00:07:47,333
I'm sick and tired of your lies!

131
00:07:48,233 --> 00:07:50,400
I'm trying to help you, Manuel.

132
00:07:50,533 --> 00:07:51,833
Please, just listen.

133
00:07:54,200 --> 00:07:55,767
The day Timo surrendered,

134
00:07:56,733 --> 00:07:58,233
I confronted him and his wife.

135
00:07:59,200 --> 00:08:00,700
I wanted to hurt them,

136
00:08:00,833 --> 00:08:01,967
and I wanted them
to feel my anger.

137
00:08:09,467 --> 00:08:11,300
<i> Are you Diana Malabanan?</i>

138
00:08:12,167 --> 00:08:13,733
<i> Yes, I am.</i>

139
00:08:13,867 --> 00:08:15,200
<i> Who are you?</i>

140
00:08:27,567 --> 00:08:28,800
<i> I'm Hazel.</i>

141
00:08:30,667 --> 00:08:32,233
<i> Jessica Cruz's mother.</i>

142
00:08:33,600 --> 00:08:35,933
<i>The girl your husband, Timo,
hit and killed.</i>

143
00:08:37,100 --> 00:08:38,100
<i> Ma'am!</i>

144
00:08:38,233 --> 00:08:39,700
<i> I'm sorry, Ma'am!</i>

145
00:08:40,067 --> 00:08:40,967
<i> Ma'am!</i>

146
00:08:41,100 --> 00:08:42,833
<i>Timo didn't mean for it
to happen.</i>

147
00:08:42,967 --> 00:08:44,367
<i> Please forgive him, Ma'am.</i>

148
00:08:44,500 --> 00:08:46,200
<i>- Let go of me.
- Sorry, Ma'am.</i>

149
00:08:46,333 --> 00:08:48,533
<i>I said let go of me!
Stand up.</i>

150
00:08:51,267 --> 00:08:52,633
<i>Don't you dare give me
your drama.</i>

151
00:08:56,600 --> 00:08:58,500
<i> Your husband is such a demon.</i>

152
00:08:59,900 --> 00:09:02,600
<i>He killed my one
and only child, Jessica.</i>

153
00:09:02,733 --> 00:09:05,167
<i>Ma'am, please, have mercy
on my baby.</i>

154
00:09:05,633 --> 00:09:07,033
<i> Don't worry.</i>

155
00:09:07,433 --> 00:09:08,967
<i> I won't hurt your baby.</i>

156
00:09:09,633 --> 00:09:10,633
<i> Just you.</i>

157
00:09:15,833 --> 00:09:19,667
When I saw Diana, I felt sorry
for her, Manuel.

158
00:09:19,933 --> 00:09:21,067
I felt so sorry for her.

159
00:09:22,267 --> 00:09:24,467
Timo is the only one
she depends on.

160
00:09:25,667 --> 00:09:27,533
And their kids,
they're still so young.

161
00:09:28,767 --> 00:09:29,700
Five...

162
00:09:30,500 --> 00:09:31,633
seven years old.

163
00:09:32,767 --> 00:09:34,433
So instead of fighting her,

164
00:09:35,133 --> 00:09:36,500
I helped her.

165
00:09:38,133 --> 00:09:39,533
You helped her?

166
00:09:41,500 --> 00:09:44,100
You helped the wife of the man
who killed our daughter?

167
00:09:45,833 --> 00:09:47,000
Why, Hazel?

168
00:09:48,000 --> 00:09:49,900
Because I'm a mother, too.

169
00:09:51,733 --> 00:09:53,133
Manuel, I couldn't do it.

170
00:09:54,767 --> 00:09:56,767
I couldn't stand
seeing another mother

171
00:09:56,900 --> 00:09:58,467
in that situation.

172
00:10:01,833 --> 00:10:03,333
<i> Ma'am Hazel?</i>

173
00:10:04,300 --> 00:10:05,967
<i> Do you need anything?</i>

174
00:10:09,800 --> 00:10:12,333
<i> Mom, stay here for a moment.</i>

175
00:10:14,767 --> 00:10:16,967
<i> I asked Timo to do something.</i>

176
00:10:17,100 --> 00:10:20,100
<i> In return, I'll help you.</i>

177
00:10:25,267 --> 00:10:26,100
<i> Here.</i>

178
00:10:29,100 --> 00:10:31,633
<i>Is there something else
you want my husband to do?</i>

179
00:10:31,767 --> 00:10:33,567
<i> He already surrendered.</i>

180
00:10:33,700 --> 00:10:35,733
<i>He already paid for what he did
to your daughter.</i>

181
00:10:35,900 --> 00:10:38,033
<i>What more do you want from him?</i>

182
00:10:38,167 --> 00:10:39,500
<i> Don't ask.</i>

183
00:10:39,633 --> 00:10:41,533
<i> Timo already agreed.</i>

184
00:10:44,767 --> 00:10:48,333
<i>Just make sure,
if you hear anything...</i>

185
00:10:49,833 --> 00:10:52,167
<i> you keep your mouth shut.</i>

186
00:10:53,300 --> 00:10:54,400
<i> Because if you don't...</i>

187
00:10:55,833 --> 00:10:59,533
<i>something bad might happen
to Timo inside the prison.</i>

188
00:11:01,933 --> 00:11:03,967
I didn't just pity Diana.

189
00:11:05,767 --> 00:11:07,833
I pitied their children, too.

190
00:11:08,000 --> 00:11:10,567
They had nothing to do
with what their father did.

191
00:11:11,633 --> 00:11:12,700
So that's your payment to Timo?

192
00:11:12,833 --> 00:11:15,067
That's why he pinned
everything on Coleen?

193
00:11:15,200 --> 00:11:17,667
You helped his wife
and his kids?

194
00:11:17,800 --> 00:11:20,500
Come on, Manuel.

195
00:11:20,633 --> 00:11:23,633
You keep accusing me
over and over.

196
00:11:23,767 --> 00:11:28,233
Timo gave his statement
before I even helped them.

197
00:11:28,367 --> 00:11:30,600
If you want, you can check
with his wife.

198
00:11:30,733 --> 00:11:32,067
Or with his mother-in-law.

199
00:11:32,200 --> 00:11:33,100
His own mother.

200
00:11:33,233 --> 00:11:34,533
I'll even go with you.

201
00:11:37,533 --> 00:11:41,567
Manuel, this hurts me, too.

202
00:11:43,100 --> 00:11:46,200
But I'm willing to set aside
what I feel.

203
00:11:47,500 --> 00:11:49,800
If it were just Timo,
he wouldn't do that.

204
00:11:51,267 --> 00:11:53,300
Timo is a man of principle.

205
00:11:54,700 --> 00:11:57,733
But he might change his mind

206
00:11:58,067 --> 00:12:00,533
because of Diana, his wife.

207
00:12:00,667 --> 00:12:02,633
What's happening to you, Hazel?

208
00:12:03,900 --> 00:12:05,500
Why did you suddenly change?

209
00:12:06,533 --> 00:12:07,500
At the last hearing,

210
00:12:07,633 --> 00:12:09,967
you were ready to tear
Coleen apart.

211
00:12:10,100 --> 00:12:11,633
Because of Jessica.

212
00:12:12,833 --> 00:12:15,767
Manuel, I don't want to ignore

213
00:12:15,933 --> 00:12:18,300
what she keeps telling me
in my dreams.

214
00:12:20,067 --> 00:12:24,400
If this is what she wants,
so we can finally have peace...

215
00:12:25,433 --> 00:12:28,467
in our lives, then fine.

216
00:12:29,500 --> 00:12:31,433
I don't care
about justice anymore.

217
00:12:33,400 --> 00:12:35,567
Manuel, I'm going
to help Coleen.

218
00:12:38,867 --> 00:12:40,933
To fulfill Jessica's
last wish...

219
00:12:42,733 --> 00:12:44,300
I'll help her.

220
00:12:46,767 --> 00:12:47,967
Let's get back together, Manuel.

221
00:12:49,400 --> 00:12:52,267
Let's rebuild our family...

222
00:12:52,400 --> 00:12:54,767
to fulfill Jessica's last wish.

223
00:12:54,900 --> 00:12:57,733
Don't use my daughter's
memory like that.

224
00:12:59,167 --> 00:13:01,833
I will never get back
together with you!

225
00:13:04,333 --> 00:13:07,500
Then the case continues.

226
00:13:09,067 --> 00:13:11,400
If you won't fulfill
Jessica's last wish,

227
00:13:11,533 --> 00:13:12,667
there's nothing more I can do.

228
00:13:14,367 --> 00:13:16,100
Coleen will rot in prison.

229
00:13:16,233 --> 00:13:18,200
My daughter will not go to jail!

230
00:13:19,600 --> 00:13:21,100
Dad, is this woman
giving you trouble again?

231
00:13:22,167 --> 00:13:23,400
No, son.

232
00:13:35,367 --> 00:13:36,933
Come on.

233
00:13:37,067 --> 00:13:39,500
<i>- It's so stubborn, yes.
- Right?</i>

234
00:13:39,633 --> 00:13:41,467
That's our boy.

235
00:13:43,600 --> 00:13:46,433
- Why does he look like that?
- Look, sweetie.

236
00:13:46,567 --> 00:13:48,067
You've been in a bad mood
since we were at the cemetery.

237
00:13:48,200 --> 00:13:49,300
What happened?

238
00:13:49,433 --> 00:13:52,233
Nothing, I just had a headache.

239
00:13:52,367 --> 00:13:53,467
A headache?

240
00:13:54,300 --> 00:13:55,200
Or you got upset?

241
00:13:56,767 --> 00:13:58,233
Both.

242
00:13:58,367 --> 00:13:59,967
Just ignore it.

243
00:14:00,100 --> 00:14:01,467
Maybe I'm just hungry.

244
00:14:03,033 --> 00:14:04,067
Come on, let's laugh a little.

245
00:14:04,200 --> 00:14:05,767
- Yes.
- Coleen, watch this.

246
00:14:05,900 --> 00:14:07,867
- Look!
- You guys watch it.

247
00:14:08,000 --> 00:14:10,200
My cheeks hurt.

248
00:14:10,333 --> 00:14:12,333
Oh, Manuel.

249
00:14:12,467 --> 00:14:16,367
Jeffrey, you went
to the cemetery?

250
00:14:16,700 --> 00:14:18,800
Why didn't you wake us up?

251
00:14:19,233 --> 00:14:20,667
Mom, it's better
you didn't come.

252
00:14:20,900 --> 00:14:22,767
You would've
gotten annoyed, too.

253
00:14:23,967 --> 00:14:26,500
- Ma'am Felma, watch this.
- What is it, Didang?

254
00:14:26,633 --> 00:14:28,167
Detective XY is live,

255
00:14:28,333 --> 00:14:31,700
talking nonsense about Coleen.

256
00:14:33,067 --> 00:14:35,000
<i> Like I said, guys,</i>

257
00:14:35,133 --> 00:14:36,800
<i> this is not confirmed, okay?</i>

258
00:14:36,933 --> 00:14:40,100
<i>Just whispers I heard from
some not-so-reliable sources.</i>

259
00:14:40,233 --> 00:14:41,367
<i> So, yes</i>

260
00:14:41,500 --> 00:14:43,600
<i>looks like this girl
might be behind bars soon,</i>

261
00:14:43,733 --> 00:14:45,167
<i> who allegedly pushed</i>

262
00:14:45,300 --> 00:14:48,700
<i>the hit-and-run victim,
Jessica Capistrano Cruz,</i>

263
00:14:48,833 --> 00:14:50,867
<i> a reason for it to get hit.</i>

264
00:14:51,000 --> 00:14:53,733
<i>The defense apparently didn't
present any evidence</i>

265
00:14:53,867 --> 00:14:58,200
<i>to contradict the statement
of the man who hit Jessica.</i>

266
00:14:58,333 --> 00:15:00,367
I'm going to jail.

267
00:15:00,500 --> 00:15:02,500
- Coleen...
- I'm going to jail.

268
00:15:04,033 --> 00:15:06,033
I'm going to jail.

269
00:15:06,167 --> 00:15:07,733
- I'm going to jail!
- Sweetie!

270
00:15:07,867 --> 00:15:09,533
- Follow your sister!
- Dear...

271
00:15:13,100 --> 00:15:14,033
- Coleen!
- Sweetie!

272
00:15:14,167 --> 00:15:16,167
- Coleen, dear?
- Coleen, sweetie!

273
00:15:16,300 --> 00:15:18,367
- Coleen?
- Coleen?

274
00:15:24,933 --> 00:15:26,100
- Coleen!
- Coleen!

275
00:15:26,233 --> 00:15:27,367
Coleen?

276
00:15:27,500 --> 00:15:28,667
Coleen!

277
00:15:30,667 --> 00:15:33,700
Thank you so much, Xander,
for granting my request again.

278
00:15:35,267 --> 00:15:36,367
I owe you so much.

279
00:15:36,500 --> 00:15:38,000
How am I ever going
to repay you?

280
00:15:38,133 --> 00:15:39,733
<i>Oh, Mrs. Cruz,
don't worry about it.</i>

281
00:15:39,867 --> 00:15:41,200
<i> I'm loaded from views anyway.</i>

282
00:15:41,333 --> 00:15:42,767
<i> Big money there.</i>

283
00:15:44,067 --> 00:15:45,967
That's good to know.

284
00:15:46,100 --> 00:15:47,833
Thanks again.

285
00:15:54,400 --> 00:15:56,267
Friend, let's eat pizza.

286
00:15:59,300 --> 00:16:00,300
By the way, friend,

287
00:16:00,433 --> 00:16:02,000
about what you said earlier.

288
00:16:02,133 --> 00:16:05,333
Are you really dreaming
about Jessica?

289
00:16:08,067 --> 00:16:09,367
Silly!

290
00:16:09,500 --> 00:16:12,033
Of course, I'm just going
along with Manuel!

291
00:16:13,067 --> 00:16:16,367
So it wasn't true
that her last wish was

292
00:16:16,500 --> 00:16:17,900
for you and Manuel
to get back together?

293
00:16:19,133 --> 00:16:20,533
Of course not.

294
00:16:21,500 --> 00:16:23,533
But I slipped it
into the conversation.

295
00:16:23,667 --> 00:16:25,633
Did he take the bait?

296
00:16:25,767 --> 00:16:28,367
Well, not yet.

297
00:16:29,800 --> 00:16:32,933
But I know Manuel
will come around.

298
00:16:33,067 --> 00:16:34,733
When Coleen's in trouble...

299
00:16:35,833 --> 00:16:38,600
and they have no way
to save that woman,

300
00:16:38,733 --> 00:16:42,300
I'm sure Manuel will turn to me.

301
00:16:42,467 --> 00:16:44,900
You're quick, friend.

302
00:16:45,033 --> 00:16:46,767
Just from hearing
Manuel's dream,

303
00:16:46,900 --> 00:16:49,133
you already hatched a plan.

304
00:16:53,600 --> 00:16:54,467
Oh, why?

305
00:16:55,500 --> 00:16:56,633
I just remembered.

306
00:16:57,533 --> 00:16:58,600
Right?

307
00:17:00,600 --> 00:17:03,500
Jessica hasn't visited me
in dreams yet.

308
00:17:04,667 --> 00:17:08,333
But she already visited
Manuel several times.

309
00:17:13,900 --> 00:17:14,900
Coleen?

310
00:17:18,133 --> 00:17:19,033
Coleen!

311
00:17:19,167 --> 00:17:20,033
Coleen!

312
00:17:20,167 --> 00:17:21,000
<i> Andrea, over here.</i>

313
00:17:21,133 --> 00:17:23,067
<i>- What?
- Mom, Dad, she's here!</i>

314
00:17:23,200 --> 00:17:24,167
Coleen!

315
00:17:24,967 --> 00:17:26,367
- Sweetie.
- Coleen.

316
00:17:26,500 --> 00:17:28,200
Dear, where are you?

317
00:17:28,333 --> 00:17:29,533
Mom, Dad, she's here!

318
00:17:30,533 --> 00:17:31,967
Coleen, sweetie!

319
00:17:32,100 --> 00:17:33,133
My child...

320
00:17:33,867 --> 00:17:36,033
Coleen, you won't go to jail.

321
00:17:36,167 --> 00:17:40,600
What Detective XY said
is just Hazel's scheme.

322
00:17:40,733 --> 00:17:42,500
Don't believe her.

323
00:17:42,633 --> 00:17:44,000
I'm going to jail.

324
00:17:44,133 --> 00:17:44,933
No!

325
00:17:45,067 --> 00:17:46,833
I'm going to jail.

326
00:17:46,967 --> 00:17:48,000
I'm going to jail.

327
00:17:48,167 --> 00:17:50,533
- Coleen, no, that's enough.
- I'm going to jail...

328
00:17:50,667 --> 00:17:52,333
Coleen, enough.

329
00:17:52,467 --> 00:17:54,467
Sweetie!

330
00:17:58,400 --> 00:18:00,067
<i> Please stop.</i>

331
00:18:05,533 --> 00:18:06,900
She's calm now, Doc Carla.

332
00:18:07,500 --> 00:18:08,700
She's asleep, too.

333
00:18:09,533 --> 00:18:12,633
Do we need to go
to the hospital?

334
00:18:14,233 --> 00:18:14,900
Okay.

335
00:18:15,367 --> 00:18:16,500
Okay, thank you, Doc.

336
00:18:18,500 --> 00:18:19,300
What did she say, Mom?

337
00:18:20,833 --> 00:18:24,367
She said we should keep her away
from social media for now.

338
00:18:25,567 --> 00:18:27,867
And avoid anything that might
trigger stress.

339
00:18:28,733 --> 00:18:30,900
Let's mute our phones, okay?

340
00:18:31,733 --> 00:18:34,667
We need to watch her,
observe her,

341
00:18:35,600 --> 00:18:37,300
and never leave her alone.

342
00:18:38,600 --> 00:18:40,567
I'll sleep beside her
tonight, Mom.

343
00:18:41,367 --> 00:18:43,700
Andeng, maybe you can stay
in the guest room instead,

344
00:18:43,833 --> 00:18:47,300
so we won't have to wake Coleen
and bring her upstairs.

345
00:18:47,433 --> 00:18:48,300
Okay, Dad.

346
00:18:49,133 --> 00:18:51,833
Sir, Ma'am, what about me?

347
00:18:51,967 --> 00:18:53,367
What can I do to help?

348
00:18:54,367 --> 00:18:55,367
Don't make noise.

349
00:18:56,600 --> 00:18:58,467
<i> And don't raise your voice.</i>

350
00:18:59,500 --> 00:19:03,100
In short, she means
you shut up for now.

351
00:19:03,233 --> 00:19:05,000
<i> Watch it.</i>

352
00:19:05,133 --> 00:19:07,733
Fine, fine,
no talking from me.

353
00:19:07,867 --> 00:19:10,733
But, Ma'am, what exactly did
the doctor say?

354
00:19:12,500 --> 00:19:14,567
The most important thing
is that...

355
00:19:16,067 --> 00:19:19,967
no one should mention anything
about the case to Coleen.

356
00:19:22,367 --> 00:19:23,600
Excuse me.

357
00:19:25,933 --> 00:19:27,133
Sir Noah.

358
00:19:27,800 --> 00:19:29,367
- Didang.
- Oh, Noah.

359
00:19:29,533 --> 00:19:30,767
How are you, guys?

360
00:19:36,100 --> 00:19:37,167
What happened to Coleen?

361
00:19:41,033 --> 00:19:45,467
The psychiatrist said
it's acute stress.

362
00:19:46,633 --> 00:19:49,533
But she's okay now.

363
00:19:53,267 --> 00:19:56,267
What about what your PI found,
Noah?

364
00:19:57,800 --> 00:19:59,533
I talked to Councilor Parce.

365
00:19:59,900 --> 00:20:03,300
Turns out the reason Timo fought
him and got fired was that

366
00:20:04,033 --> 00:20:08,533
he caught the councilor
cheating on his wife.

367
00:20:08,833 --> 00:20:10,233
He tried to bribe him...

368
00:20:11,400 --> 00:20:13,000
but Timo refused.

369
00:20:14,367 --> 00:20:17,667
He said he'd tell
Mrs. Parce everything.

370
00:20:18,933 --> 00:20:22,133
- Meaning?
- He's an upright person.

371
00:20:23,433 --> 00:20:25,967
Has conviction and principles.

372
00:20:27,300 --> 00:20:31,000
That's why it will be hard
to break his credibility.

373
00:20:31,133 --> 00:20:33,200
But I still refuse to believe

374
00:20:33,333 --> 00:20:35,567
he actually saw Coleen
push Jessica!

375
00:20:35,733 --> 00:20:36,700
Me, too.

376
00:20:37,400 --> 00:20:38,667
When I talked to him,

377
00:20:38,800 --> 00:20:40,600
he couldn't even look me
straight in the eye.

378
00:20:40,733 --> 00:20:42,767
Well, for him to go against
his own principles,

379
00:20:44,233 --> 00:20:45,667
something must have changed,

380
00:20:46,167 --> 00:20:48,033
after he surrendered
to the police.

381
00:20:49,900 --> 00:20:51,300
Hazel!

382
00:20:52,300 --> 00:20:55,367
If Timo's record is that clean,
does that mean

383
00:20:56,000 --> 00:20:57,933
there's a big chance
we'll lose the case?

384
00:20:59,167 --> 00:21:00,233
Coleen can't go to jail.

385
00:21:00,367 --> 00:21:01,833
She cannot go to jail!

386
00:21:03,367 --> 00:21:05,500
- Mom, she's so young!
- Son...

387
00:21:05,633 --> 00:21:06,800
Son, your voice.

388
00:21:06,933 --> 00:21:08,800
Coleen might wake up.

389
00:21:08,967 --> 00:21:09,733
Okay?

390
00:21:09,867 --> 00:21:11,500
That's enough.

391
00:21:11,633 --> 00:21:12,933
I have an idea.

392
00:21:14,933 --> 00:21:18,800
If Hazel paid Timo
to destroy Coleen,

393
00:21:19,500 --> 00:21:23,200
then I'll pay Timo
to take everything back.

394
00:21:23,833 --> 00:21:24,867
I can offer more.

395
00:21:25,000 --> 00:21:28,033
I can double or even triple
whatever Hazel gave him.

396
00:21:28,167 --> 00:21:30,567
We're not doing
what Hazel did, Noah.

397
00:21:31,633 --> 00:21:34,533
We haven't even proven
our suspicions yet.

398
00:21:35,500 --> 00:21:37,867
If we try that,
Timo could turn on us,

399
00:21:38,300 --> 00:21:42,167
say in court that we attempted
to bribe him.

400
00:21:42,333 --> 00:21:44,600
That would hurt
Coleen's case even more.

401
00:22:06,200 --> 00:22:09,100
<i>I can convince Timo
to clear Coleen's name,</i>

402
00:22:09,233 --> 00:22:11,533
<i> and fulfill Jessica's wish.</i>

403
00:22:12,900 --> 00:22:13,833
Jeff.

404
00:22:16,367 --> 00:22:17,167
Andeng.

405
00:22:19,400 --> 00:22:21,767
Forgive me, but I have
to leave you again.

406
00:22:26,767 --> 00:22:29,500
I need to do this
to save Coleen.

407
00:22:31,200 --> 00:22:32,733
What do you mean
by leave, Manuel?

408
00:22:41,467 --> 00:22:42,533
<i> Hello, Manuel.</i>

409
00:22:42,667 --> 00:22:45,433
Have you thought about the help
I'm offering for Coleen?

410
00:22:47,333 --> 00:22:48,133
Help?

411
00:22:48,300 --> 00:22:50,867
That's not help, Hazel.

412
00:22:51,000 --> 00:22:52,100
That's a trap.

413
00:22:52,500 --> 00:22:56,400
I'll use my money
to get what I want.

414
00:22:56,533 --> 00:22:59,400
I don't want you
to go back to Hazel.

415
00:22:59,533 --> 00:23:00,733
I don't want that either, Felma.

416
00:23:00,867 --> 00:23:02,700
I don't, I really don't.

417
00:23:03,333 --> 00:23:05,000
But we don't have
any other choice.

418
00:23:05,133 --> 00:23:08,333
This is the only way
to set Coleen free.

419
00:23:09,933 --> 00:23:11,700
Three hundred thousand pesos.

420
00:23:11,833 --> 00:23:13,033
All of that is for you.
